<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-1235] Enable server to indefinitely retry on controlled shutdown</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-1235</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Today the kafka server can exit silently if it hits an exception that is swallowed during controlled shut down or &quot;controlled.shutdown.max.retries&quot; has been exhausted. It is better to add an option to let it retry indefinitely.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also will fix some other loose-check bugs on socket-closing logic.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
